data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value: Alongside Acts of Parliament will be a coloured dot, to assist in being able to tell Acts apart by their status. Collections of documents are marked with a book, and individual documents of an Act are marked with an icon of a piece of paper. The following is a decoding table. Red 'R' - Failed This indicates a Bill which failed three readings, or was not fully read by the end of the session. Orange 'D' - Destroyed This indicates an Act which has been lost after a data loss incident. They are considered repealed. Yellow 'P' - Pending This indicates a Bill that is currently in the process of parliamentary approval or Royal Assent. Green 'IF' - In force This indicates an Act that is in force, as originally enacted. Blue 'S' - Spent This indicates an Act which has served the purpose for which the Act was enacted. Purple 'A' - Amended This indicates an Act that is in force, with amendments made to it. Black 'R' - Repealed This indicates an Act that is no longer in force.

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value: Each entry of an Act of Parliament is highlighted by a colour. This colour represents the originating party or entity. Red refers to the Communist Party of Baustralia (formerly Worker's Party of Baustralia), Green refers to the Liberal Party of Baustralia (formerly Grand Union of Leftist Parties), Blue refers to the Conservative Party of Baustralia, Purple refers to the Sovereign, in accordance with the Monarchy (Powers) Act, 3 John 1 c. 14. Acts of Parliament which have been destroyed are marked in black.
